properties.DESCRIPTION: This project is a joint project with the lead being the City of University Place.  The City of Tacoma portion is from S Orchard St to Tacoma Mall Blvd.  The design is underway for the complete project.  The construction will be phased and construction start date is the anticipated date for Phase 1 to begin, while the construction end date is the anticipated date for phase 2 to end.  Phase 1 is from S Orchard St to Washington.  Phase 2 is from Washington to Tacoma Mall Boulevard.  The project will include a new pavement surface, curb ramp upgrades, and signal interconnect.

Streetscape project on S38th Street from South J Street to S Fawcett and South G Street from S37th to S38th Streets, including new sidewalks, curb and gutter, crosswalks, one traffic signal, gateway art/signs, and grind and overlay of pavement. S Yakima Avenue from S37th to S38th will also receive pavement grind and overlay. ES and Tacoma Water will be replacing some of their mains within the project area. Tacoma Power will be replacing their poles and power lines with new taller poles.

properties.PROJECTNAME: S. 56th Street and Cirque Drive Improvements Phase 2
properties.DESCRIPTION: Phase 2 construction includes upgrading existing sidewalks, driveways, and curb ramps to current ADA standards where needed, landscaping, traffic signal interconnect, controller, illumination upgrades, and grind and overlay on S. 56th Street.  Bicycle accommodations will be included on S. 54th  St. and other streets necessary to make the connection between the South Tacoma Sounder Station and the Tacoma Mall Transit Center.

This project will replace three sections of the Puyallup River Bridge from the intersection of Puyallup and Portland to the truss span that goes over the Puyallup River.  The new structure as determined design build team is a continuous concrete girder bridge.

The project will improve E. 64th roadway from McKinley Ave E to Pacific Ave. The project consists of grinding and replacing the road, adding bike lanes, replacing sidewalks and curb ramps with ramps meeting ADA standards, upgrade the stormwater system, upgrading the illumination system and include LED lighting, add rain gardens, add parallel parking lane the length of the project and improving signal communication by interconnecting the signals at McKinley and Pacific Ave

properties.PROJECTNAME: Pacific Avenue at SR7 Safety Improvement
properties.DESCRIPTION: Improve the visibility of traffic signal heads and improve the phasing, timing, and coordination between signals. Upgrade to accessible countdown pedestrian signals and push buttons, improve crosswalks, upgrade ramps at each corner to meet ADA Standard, and upgrade signs.

The Schuster Parkway project will replace an existing sidewalk with a shared-use promenade along Schuster Parkway from S 4th to N 30th and McCarver.  The project will include elevated sections.  The project will also improve the intersection at S 4th St. and Schuster Parkway

properties.PROJECTNAME: Links to Opportunity - Transit Oriented Development 1st/Division/MLK
properties.DESCRIPTION: This project consists of improvements between curb and right of way limits along the route of the Tacoma Link Expansion.  This includes improvements on N. 1st Street between N E St and Division Ave, Division Avenue between N. 1st Street and MLK Jr Way, and MLK Jr. Way between Division Ave and S. 19th St.  This project also includes Equity and Empowerment and may include amenities such as wayfinding signs and complete street concepts outside, but connected to the link extension route.

This project will create a 1/3 mile long pedestrian and bike trail along the former BNSF Railway line running from 21st to 23rd.  Plantings, storm water improvements and lighting will be part of the project.

properties.PROJECTNAME: First Creek Middle School Safe Routes to School
properties.DESCRIPTION: This project will install a HAWK signal and beacons, crosswalk signage and markings, and sidewalk improvements.  The location of infrastructure improvement is on Portland Avenue near East 52nd Street.

properties.DESCRIPTION: Streetscape project on S38th Street from South J Street to S Fawcett and South G Street and South Yakima from S37th to S39th Streets, including new sidewalks, curb and gutter, crosswalks, signal improvements, gateway art/signs, and grind and overlay of pavement. ES and Tacoma Water will be replacing some of their mains within the project area. Tacoma Power will be replacing their poles and power lines with new taller poles. The Festival Street, South Yakima Ave from S. 38th to S. 39th Streets will also include colored concrete pavement.
Project will improve the intersection at S. 21st and Fawcett, and add bulb outs on Fawcett Ave between S. 21st and S 19th to improve active transportation and add new ADA accessible ramps.

This project includes the construction of a new roadway section along E. Fairbanks St. from E. Howe St. to E. M St. and again from E. Portland Ave. to E. Roosevelt Ave.  A grind and overlay of the roadway surface will occur along E. Fairbanks St. from E. M St. to just east of E. N St. where the hill is too steep for a new roadway section.  New catch basins will be installed at the E. N St./E. Fairbanks St. intersection, and catch basin maintenance will occur at all other intersections as needed.  Two new large inlet structures will be installed at the bottom of the hill along E. Fairbanks St. near First Creek.  Additionally, a sanitary sewer line re-route will be constructed along E. Fairbanks St. near First Creek.  Finally, curb ramps will be improved at all intersections and curb/gutter work will be performed along E. Fairbanks St. as needed for catch basin maintenance/installation or roadway construction.

properties.DESCRIPTION: Project will construct needed safety improvements along South Tacoma Way/ E 26th Street corridor. the project will include a variety of safety improvements including signal system upgrades, flashing yellow arrow signal heads, countdown pedestrian signals, and audible pedestrian push buttons. properties.PROJECTNAME: Revitalizing Tacoma's Brewery District with Complete Streets: Phase I
properties.DESCRIPTION: The project will deploy traffic calming measures along Fawcett, from 19th St. to 6th Ave., consisting of new curb ramps, curb extensions, pedestrian refuge islands, mid-block crossings, and other upgraded crossings.  Approximately 9 blocks of the 13 blocks included in the project along Fawcett will receive a grind/overlay.  ADA accessibility will be improved and bicycle detection/APS will be implemented.  This project also includes a striped bicycle lane along the included blocks of S. 15th St., from Yakima to Fawcett, in addition to other bicycle amenities.

This project will install pedestrian crossing improvements along North 21st Street between Proctor Street and Pearl Street. The project will construct enhancements to three existing crossings at un-signalized intersections (Shirley, Cheyenne and Mason) to increase driver awareness of pedestrians wanting to cross North 21st Street and the frequency of pedestrian crossing options. Crossing treatments at these un-signalized intersections will include flashing beacons, ADA compliant curb ramps, crosswalk markings and signage. Signalized intersection crossings at Proctor, Stevens and Orchard will also be improved with ADA curb ramps, crosswalk markings, and adjustments to pedestrian push buttons.
